# Hardware Evidence

Evidence is not one thing.

Each stage has a different kind of evidence. Validation is the decision made
after checking that evidence.

| Stage | Requirement/Obligation | Contract | Evidence examples | Validation question |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Requirement | What must exist | locked req / review rule | `requirements.md`, locked req JSON | Is the requirement explicit enough to test? |
| RTL | What RTL must implement | compile/lint/interface contract | RTL diff, `rtl_compile.json` | Does the implementation exist and compile? |
| Lint | What style/structure must hold | lint rules | `dut_lint.json`, lint log | Are there blocking lint issues? |
| TB | What must be observed | scenario/scoreboard contract | cocotb/pyuvm test, scoreboard code | Does the TB observe the obligation? |
| Sim | What actually ran | simulator pass/fail contract | `results.xml`, sim log | Did the run really execute and pass? |
| Scoreboard | Expected vs observed | FL/model/expected contract | `scoreboard_events.jsonl` | Did RTL match expected behavior? |
| Coverage | Which cases were exercised | coverage plan / bins | `coverage.json`, coverage report | Did the important case run? |
| VCD/Waveform | Cycle-level trace | dump/manifest contract | `.vcd`, `.fst`, wave manifest | Can we inspect the root cause? |
| Formal | Property proof | SVA / formal property | `.sva`, proof log, `formal_status.json` | Was this property proven? |
| Signoff | Evidence bundle closure | signoff checklist | `truth_coverage.json`, signoff report | Is the chosen bundle complete? |

## PASS means different things

```text
RTL compile PASS
  means the code compiles.

Simulation PASS
  means the tests that ran did not fail.

Scoreboard PASS
  means observed values matched expected values.

Coverage PASS
  means selected bins or goals were hit.

Formal PASS
  means a specific property was proven.

Signoff PASS
  means the required evidence bundle is complete.
```

Do not collapse these into "tests passed."

Prefer:

```text
Simulation passed, scoreboard rows passed, the target edge-case coverage bin
was hit, and a VCD was saved for debug.
```
